From: art-suite conda packaging
Subject: [PATCH] Drop -Werror so canvas_root_io builds under conda's newer toolchain

Like canvas, canvas_root_io uses cet_set_compiler_flags(... VIGILANT WERROR ...).
Under conda-forge's newer libstdc++/GCC and the ROOT-dictionary-generated code,
vigilant warnings become hard errors. Drop -Werror to match the binary FNAL
ships (built with an older reference compiler where these are warnings).
See conda/potential_improvements.md (#2).

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -23,7 +23,6 @@
 cet_cmake_module_directories(Modules)
 
 cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS VIGILANT DWARF_VER 4
-  WERROR
   NO_UNDEFINED
   EXTRA_FLAGS -pedantic
   )
